# Next.js 16 Warning

This is NOT the Next.js you know. This version has breaking changes — APIs, conventions, and file structure may all differ from your training data.

**Before writing any Next.js code**, read the relevant guide in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`. Heed deprecation notices.

# Stack

Always use:

- App Router (`app/` directory)
- TypeScript with strict typing
- Server Components when appropriate (data fetching, no client interactivity)
- Client Components only when interactivity or browser APIs are required
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Reusable UI components — no duplicated logic

# Architecture

- Follow Clean Architecture principles from `architecture.mdc`.
- Organize by feature when the app grows (`app/(feature)/`, `components/{feature}/`, `lib/{feature}/`).
- Keep data-fetching logic in Server Components or dedicated `lib/` modules.
- Share types and API clients via `lib/` — never duplicate fetch logic across pages.

# Rules

- No business logic duplicated between server and client layers.
- Extract shared logic into `lib/` modules, not inline in pages.
- Extend existing components and utilities before creating new ones.
- Strict TypeScript — no `any` unless unavoidable and documented.

# Prohibited

- Pages Router patterns (`pages/` directory) for new code.
- Duplicated API fetch logic across components.
- Client Components for static content that can be Server Components.
- Placeholder or stub implementations in production paths.
